# Multi-Platform Targets & Testing

This project ships on **iOS**, **macOS**, and **tvOS**. Every change must account for all three.

## Platform Targeting

- Before modifying any file, verify which targets it belongs to. Never add or remove target membership unintentionally.
- Use `#if os(iOS)`, `#if os(macOS)`, `#if os(tvOS)`, or `#if targetEnvironment(...)` when behaviour must differ per platform.
- When adding new files, include them in **all applicable targets** unless there is a clear platform-specific reason not to.
- UI components must respect each platform's interaction model (touch, pointer, remote/focus).

## Testing & Regression Prevention

- **Test every target**: after any feature or bug fix, build and verify on iOS, macOS, and tvOS. Do not assume a change that works on one platform works on the others.
- **Meaningful tests**: validate actual behaviour, not just compilation. Confirm UI renders, navigation works, and data flows correctly on each platform.
- **Regression awareness**: when fixing a bug, verify the fix does not break existing functionality on any target. If a change is platform-specific, still smoke-test the other platforms.
- **Conditional code**: any `#if os(...)` block must be tested on the included *and* excluded platforms to ensure both paths are correct.
